data.description:
Welcome home. This 3 bedroom 1 bath home is loaded with charm and character. Conveniently located with easy commutes, and easy access to the foothills, it's in the perfect work play location.  
As you walk in the front door, from the front porch, you are welcomed into a huge living room filled with light from three huge windows. The hardwood floors throughout the home have been well cared for. The dining room, kitchen, and breakfast bar are open to the living room. The kitchen features glass inserts in the upper cabinets, a brick wall, granite counter tops, and a skylight. Right off the dining room there's a bedroom which could be a perfect light, bright office at the front of the home. Down the hall there's another good sized bedroom that has a small walk-in closet with built-ins. The bathroom is mid hall - convenient to the 2nd and Primary bedrooms and away from the living room, dining, and kitchen area. The Primary bedroom is at the back of the house, it features a large window that looks out into the private back yard, and also has a small walk in closet with built-ins. Every bedroom has a ceiling fan and window treatments. The large laundry & utility room has built in cabinets, lots of space, and tons of light. Through the back door you'll find a private back yard with fire pit, and the 2-car detached garage. Accessed through the alley, it's not only a garage, there is a large bonus space for workshop &/or yoga studio.
